<a name="task4"></a>
## 🎯 Task 4 — Object Detection & Tracking (TITAN)

### What is this?
A real-time desktop application that opens your webcam (or a video file) and detects + tracks every object it sees — persons, smartphones, laptops, cups, chairs, wires, bottles, and 70+ more objects.

It also detects **body parts** specifically:
- 🖐 **Hands** (left and right separately, all 21 finger joints)
- 🦵 **Legs and feet** (hip → knee → ankle → heel → foot)
- 💪 **Full body skeleton** (shoulders, elbows, wrists, hips, knees, ankles — 33 points)

TITAN stands for **Tracking & Identification Technology for Autonomous Networks** *(custom name I gave it)*.

### How does it work? (Simple explanation)

TITAN uses **THREE AI engines running at the same time** on every video frame:

---

#### Engine 1 — YOLOv8 (Object Detection)

YOLO stands for **You Only Look Once**. It's one of the fastest and most accurate object detection models ever created.

```
How YOLO works:
  → Divides the image into a grid
  → For each grid cell, predicts:
      • Is there an object here?
      • What class is it? (person, phone, cup, etc.)
      • Where exactly is it? (bounding box coordinates)
      • How confident is it? (0% to 100%)
  → All of this happens in a single forward pass through the neural network
  → That's why it's called "You Only Look Once"
```

I used **YOLOv8** — the latest generation from Ultralytics, pre-trained on the **COCO dataset** (80 object classes, 330,000 images).

**ByteTrack** is added on top of YOLO to give each detected object a unique **tracking ID (#1, #2, #3...)** that follows it across frames, even if it briefly disappears.

---

#### Engine 2 — MediaPipe Pose (Body Skeleton)

Google's MediaPipe Pose detects **33 body landmarks** on a person — every joint from nose to toe.

```
How MediaPipe Pose works:
  → Takes the video frame as input
  → Runs a lightweight neural network (BlazePose)
  → Outputs x,y coordinates for 33 body points
  → Each point has a "visibility" score (0 to 1)
  → I filter points with visibility > 0.4 to avoid drawing bad guesses
```

I color-coded the body parts:
- 🟠 **Orange** = Left hand (wrist, fingers)
- 🩵 **Cyan** = Right hand (wrist, fingers)
- 🟣 **Purple** = Left leg (hip → knee → ankle → foot)
- 🟢 **Green** = Right leg (hip → knee → ankle → foot)

---

#### Engine 3 — MediaPipe Hands (Detailed Hand Detection)

MediaPipe Hands is a dedicated hand detector that finds **21 precise landmarks** per hand — every knuckle and fingertip.

```
How MediaPipe Hands works:
  → First detects the palm using a fast detector
  → Then zooms in and runs a landmark model on just the hand region
  → Returns 21 (x,y,z) coordinates per hand
  → Supports up to 4 hands simultaneously
  → Also tells you: is this the left or right hand?
```

This is more detailed than Pose alone — it can tell when fingers are bent, extended, or spread.

---

#### What happens every single frame:

```
📷 Camera captures frame
        ↓
🔲 Draw grid (if enabled)
        ↓
🦴 MediaPipe Pose → draw skeleton + highlight hands & legs
        ↓
✋ MediaPipe Hands → draw 21-point hand landmarks
        ↓
🎯 YOLOv8 → detect all objects → draw bounding boxes
        ↓
📍 ByteTrack → assign tracking IDs + draw motion trails
        ↓
📊 HUD overlay → FPS, object count, top detections
        ↓
🖥️ Display final frame
```

### Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| 80 COCO classes | Detects person, phone, laptop, cup, chair, bottle, wire, remote, scissors, car, dog, and 70+ more |
| Body skeleton | 33-point full body skeleton drawn live |
| Hand detection | 21-point per-hand landmarks, left/right labeled separately |
| Leg detection | Hip-knee-ankle-foot chain drawn and labeled |
| Motion trails | Ghost path shows where each tracked object has moved |
| Confidence bar | Each box has a color-coded confidence bar (green = high, red = low) |
| Rule-of-thirds grid | Toggle a composition grid overlay (press G) |
| HUD panel | Live FPS, object count, top 5 detected classes |
| Webcam or video file | Works with live camera or any .mp4 / .avi file |

### Keyboard controls (in the detection window)

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `P` | Pause / Resume |
| `Q` | Quit and close window |
| `G` | Toggle rule-of-thirds grid overlay |
| `T` | Toggle motion trails |
| `S` | Toggle body skeleton |

### What I used (Technologies)

| Tool | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `Python` | Core programming language |
| `YOLOv8 (Ultralytics)` | Pre-trained object detection model — detects 80 object classes |
| `ByteTrack` | Object tracking algorithm — assigns persistent IDs across frames |
| `MediaPipe Pose` | Google's body pose estimation — 33 body landmarks including hands and legs |
| `MediaPipe Hands` | Google's hand tracking — 21 finger joint landmarks per hand |
| `OpenCV` | Opens webcam/video, processes frames, draws all boxes and overlays |
| `NumPy` | Handles numerical operations on image arrays |
| `Tkinter` | Control panel desktop UI |
| `Threading` | Runs detection in background so UI doesn't freeze |

### Install & Run
```bash
pip install ultralytics opencv-python numpy
pip uninstall mediapipe -y
pip install mediapipe==0.10.9
python detector_v2.py
```

> **Note:** MediaPipe must be version `0.10.9` specifically. Newer versions removed the `solutions` API that Pose and Hands use.

> On first run, YOLOv8 will auto-download the model weights (~6MB for Nano, ~22MB for Small). This only happens once.

